      "writtenOn": "2021-04-12T19:06:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Major: this will result in releasing SQ spot, so we may end up with partially submitted Run *which* isn\u0027t finalized.\n\nI think I forgot about this when reviewing prior CL, sorry.\nMy proposal:\nIF a Run has at least 1 CL already submitted \u0026\u0026 SQ spot has to be released,\nTHEN Run submission must be permanently failed.\n\nWDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 286,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 287,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "0b987a05197c4ceb054885bbb74114a48ced8247",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f6304f0e_3187540e",
        "filename": "cv/internal/run/impl/handler/submit.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 287,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-13T01:14:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In general, I like what you proposed and that should work without an issue since we have CL-level retries. However, I\u0027m not sure how things will play out for large CL stacks. imagine a CL stack of 100+ CLs, assuming each CL take 1s to submit(it is the P50 for Gerrit submit RPC if I get the metric correct), we would easily get DeadlineExceeded error here for the first attempt since GAE timeout is 60s. If we mark it as transient, it is possible for CV to submit everything upon second retry although it means there\u0027s a short window that a RUN is partially submitted and waiting for the acquiring the submit queue again.",
      "parentUuid": "8569bc18_1f66b138",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 286,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 287,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "0b987a05197c4ceb054885bbb74114a48ced8247",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4d146b95_c1319c04",
        "filename": "cv/internal/run/impl/handler/submit.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 287,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-13T13:03:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. CV TQ handler can take 10 minutes.\n  -\u003e I don\u0027t recall if it get it by default, so we may need to create a dedicated service for RM operations.\n\n2. Oh, I actually forgot to cap Run by 100 CLs -- will do so 😊\n\n\n\u003e If we mark it as transient, it is possible for CV to submit everything upon second retry although it means there\u0027s a short window that a RUN is partially submitted and waiting for the acquiring the submit queue again.\n\nIMO, the big problem is NOT the waiting for re-acquire (though ideally, there is no waiting). It is that another Run can be submitted in the mean time.\n\nHence, my proposal above, which combined with 10 minutes, should provide better service than CQD.\n\n\nAs a follow up, we can speed up re-acquisition by:\n  (a) add new \"taskID\" in Run.Submission\n  (b) Run.Submission.TaskID is set to value from X-CloudTasks-TaskName header (need to be exposed in server.tq.TaskExecutionInfo https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/9d9b06541571/server/tq/dispatcher.go#430)\n  (c) on retry the X-CloudTasks-TaskName will match the one stored in the server.tq.TaskExecutionInfo, so there is no need to wait for the deadline.\n  (d) deadline now can be made larger, e.g. 20 minutes.",
      "parentUuid": "f6304f0e_3187540e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 286,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 287,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "0b987a05197c4ceb054885bbb74114a48ced8247",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a660b52b_3226020b",
        "filename": "cv/internal/run/impl/handler/submit.go",
